# this folder contains the list of all diagnostics

if you want to regenerate the diagnostics file (toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/DiagRegistry.kro) you can run the following command from the root of the repo:

```bash
./scripts/diag_codegen.py toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/CodeGen.diag.toml \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Internal.diag.toml      \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Linker.diag.toml        \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Lowering.diag.toml      \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Memory.diag.toml        \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Optimization.diag.toml  \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Portability.diag.toml   \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Resolution.diag.toml    \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Semantic.diag.toml      \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Syntax.diag.toml        \
    toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/gens/Uncategorized.diag.toml > toolchain/Core/Diagnostics/DiagRegistry.kro
```

the following categories are used:
    - Syntax [S]
    - Uncategorized Errors [U]
    - Code Generation Errors [C]
    - Memory [M]
    - Resolution [R]
    - Linker [L]
    - Semantic [SC]
    - Portability/Platform [P]
    - Lowering [CL]
    - Optimization [OPT]
    - Internal [I]
With the following severity levels:
    - Ignored [I]
    - Remark  [R]
    - Verbose [V]
    - Note    [N]
    - Debug   [D]
    - Warning [W]
    - Error   [E]
    - Fatal   [F]